 the explosive politics and turmoil of the time in creative and socially conscious ways. Outlining how toys shaped and were shaped by radical visions, Goldberg locates the moment Americans first came to understand the world of toys—from Barbie to G.I. Joe—as much more than child’s play.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBlack dollsxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aBlack dollszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aChildrenxSocial life and customsy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aChildrenzUnited StatesxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aParentingxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aPlayxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aToysxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aToysxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aToyszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWar toysxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027102?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027102/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023